# ETL and Training Cron Jobs
# Format: minute hour day month weekday command
# Note: Environment variables from .env file need to be loaded in the script

# Run ETL job daily at 2:00 AM
# This will extract data from 3 days ago (default ETL_DAYS_LOOKBACK=3)
# Using bash -c to ensure proper environment and shell execution
0 2 * * * root bash -c "cd /app && /app/scripts/run_etl_and_train.sh"

# Optional: Run ETL job at a different time (uncomment if needed)
# 0 3 * * * root /app/scripts/run_etl_and_train.sh

# Note: The script run_etl_and_train.sh will:
# 1. Run ETL job to extract and process data
# 2. If ETL succeeds, automatically run training
# 3. Log everything to /var/log/etl/etl_and_train_YYYYMMDD_HHMMSS.log

